	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />And an initial save state, which would probably make your tester blow up.
<br />
<br />If all you are doing is testing the movies for rapid button presses, writing a native program that parses the movie file should be a lot easier than programming a NES game that polls the inputs. Plus, it will be able to scan faster than real-time.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


