		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Nesticle also supports PCs that are considered slow today but which were affordable during the late 1990s bull market, when unemployment was low. A lot of people haven't been able to afford a new PC since. FCE Ultra, on the other hand, has the (nice-sounding but CPU-hogging) Festalon audio engine.

		

